\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Application Installation (AppInstall) is used to install a Windows\'ae CE\endash 
based application onto a Windows CE\endash based device. This paper discusses AppInstall and is specifically targeted to creating a setup program that supports multiple devices
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li-1800\ri0\sb200\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin-1800\itap0 \b\f28\fs40\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Overview
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Application Installation (AppInstall) is the mechanism used to install Windows CE\endash 
based applications onto a Windows CE\endash based device. AppInstall supports multiple installation methods, such as desktop-to-device, web-to-device, storage card-to-device, and device-to-device.
\par AppInstall is comprised of three components:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li405\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx405\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls11\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls11
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls11\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc1\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr1\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin405\itap0 {CAB Wizard (CabWiz) is the desktop tool that packages application binaries into a single Windows CE .cab file, which is the file format for distributing multiple f
iles. CabWiz is used by the application developer and is part of the Windows CE software development kit (SDK).
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls19
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls19\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc1\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr1\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {Application Manager (CeAppMgr) is the desktop Microsoft\'ae ActiveSync component that provides a desktop-to-device application management tool. It is responsible for adding and removing applications on the Windows CE\endash 
based device and deleting the application files from the desktop computer. Application Manager is used by both the application developer and the end user and is included with every installation of ActiveSync.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls12\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls12
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls12\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc1\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr1\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {WCELoad is the Windows CE tool that unpacks a Windows CE .cab file to install an application on a device. WCELoad is used by the end user and is included with most Windows CE\endash based devices.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {The Application Installation documentation is part of the Windows CE SDK Programmer\rquote 
s Guide. This documentation includes samples of the input file to CabWiz (the CabWiz .inf file) and the input file to CeAppMgr (the CeAppMgr .ini file).
\par The CabWiz .inf file is a modified version of the Win32\'ae .inf file format. For more information on the Win32 .inf file format, see the Win32 Platform SDK.
\par This paper describes how to create a setup program that supports multiple devices and assumes knowledge of the Windows CE CabWiz .inf file format.
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li-1800\ri0\sb200\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin-1800\itap0 \b\f28\fs40\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Supporting Multiple Devices
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {The CabWiz .inf file is the setup script file that specifies the files to copy an
d the registry settings to make. CabWiz uses the application developer\rquote s .inf file and the application binaries to create one or more .cab files. 
\par If the application is device-independent\emdash for example, a set of help files\emdash then a single .cab file that is device-independent can be created. If the application contains device-specific files\emdash for example, .exe or .dll files\emdash 
then multiple .cab files can be created with a single CabWiz .inf setup file, with each .cab file supporting a specific device. The method to 
create multiple platform-specific .cab files from a single CabWiz .inf file is to use platform labels and the CEDevice key in the CabWiz .inf file.
\par The platform labels tell CabWiz how many .cab files to generate, where to get the CPU-specific binary files,
 and the platform information to incorporate into the .cab file. This information is used by the Application Manager to determine the appropriate .cab file to install on the end user\rquote s device.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {Platform labels are unique labels that are appended to specific sections in the CabWiz .inf file\emdash 
for example, HPC_SH3, PPC_MIPS, or HPCPRO_ARM. The main section that differentiates the platforms is the CEDevice section, which allows for device-specific information, namely, the processor type, the device types\emdash Handheld PC or Palm-size PC
\emdash supported, and the Windows CE version supported. These platform labels also need to be specified in the command-line parameters when invoking CabWiz.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {Here is an example from a CabWiz .inf file that supports multiple platforms. This example only displays the CEDevice and SourceDisksNames sections.
\par }\pard\plain \s39\ql \li0\ri0\sl-220\slmult0\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\f29\fs16\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par [CEDevice.HPC_SH3]\tab \tab \tab \tab ; targeted to the H/PC with the SH3 processor
\par ProcessorType\tab = 10003\tab \tab \tab \tab ; processor value for SH3
\par UnsupportedPlatforms = Palm PC,Jupiter\tab ; this .cab will not install on Palm-size PC or H/PC 
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab ; with Pro Edition software
\par 
\par [CEDevice.PPC_MIPS]\tab \tab \tab \tab ; targeted to Palm-size PC with the MIPS processor
\par ProcessorType\tab = 4000\tab \tab \tab \tab ; processor value for MIPS R3900
\par UnsupportedPlatforms = HPC,Jupiter\tab \tab ; this .cab will not install on H/PC or H/PC with Pro
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab ; Edition software 
\par 
\par [CEDevice.HPCPRO_ARM]\tab \tab \tab ; targeted to H/PC with Pro Edition software and the
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab ; StrongARM processor
\par ProcessorType\tab = 2577\tab \tab \tab \tab ; processor value for ARM
\par UnsupportedPlatforms = Palm PC,HPC\tab ; this .cab will not install on Palm-size PC or H/PC
\par 
\par [SourceDisksNames]\tab \tab \tab ; source dir for CPU-independent files for all created .cab files
\par 1 = ,"common files",,common
\par [SourceDisksNames.HPC_SH3]\tab \tab ; source dir for H/PC SH3 files
\par 2 = ,"HPC SH3 files",,hpc\\sh3
\par [SourceDisksNames.PPC_MIPS]\tab ; source dir for Palm-size PC MIPS files
\par 2 = ,"PPC MIPS files",,ppc\\mips
\par [SourceDisksNames.HPCPRO_ARM]\tab ; source dir for H/PC with Pro Edition software ARM files
\par 2 = ,"HPCPro ARM files",,hpcpro\\arm
\par 
\par [SourceDisksFiles]
\par ; help and readme
\par MyApp.HTM = 1
\par MyApp.TXT = 1
\par ; application binary
\par MyApp.EXE = 2
\par MyApp.DLL = 2
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {In the CEDevice section, the above example creates three .cab files:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls13\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls13
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls13\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc1\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr1\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {HPC_SH3.cab for the Handheld PC using the SH3 processor.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls13\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls13
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls13\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc2\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr2\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {PPC_MIPS.cab for the Palm-size PC using the MIPS processor.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls14\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls14
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls14\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc1\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr1\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {HPCPRO_ARM.cab for the Handheld PC running Pro Edition software using the ARM processor.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {In the SourceDisksNames and SourceDisksFiles sections, the source directory for device-independent common files (such as readme or help files) is in the .\\
common directory and is referenced with a directory identifier of 1. The source directory for the device-specific files (the .exe and .dll files) are located in the various platform-specific directories (.\\hpc\\
sh3 for example), and are referenced with a directory identifier of 2.
\par CabWiz needs to be invoked with the appropriate platform labels, for example,\line }{\i Cabwiz.exe \'93<INF_path>\\MyApp.INF\'94 /cpu HPC_SH3 PPC_MIPS HPCPRO_ARM}{. This creates three device-specific .cab files:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls15\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls15
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls15\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc1\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr1\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {MyApp.HPC_SH3.cab
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls15\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls15
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls15\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc2\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr2\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {MyApp.PPC_MIPS.cab
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\tx450{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls15\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls15
\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls15\pnrauth1\pnrdate-1506206856\pnrstart0\pnrxst1\pnrxst0\pnrxst183\pnrxst240\pnrstop4\pnrstart1\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrrgb0\pnrstop9\pnrstart2\pnrnfc23\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0
\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc3\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrnfc0\pnrstop18\pnrstart3\pnrpnbr3\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0
\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrpnbr0\pnrstop36\adjustright\rin0
\lin360\itap0 {MyApp.HPCPRO_ARM.cab
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {
With a single CabWiz .inf file, the application developer can create multiple device-specific .cab files. These .cab files can be directly downloaded to the device. For example, an end user can use Pocket Internet Explorer on a Windows CE\endash 
based device to download the appropriate .cab file and run the file on the device to install the application.
\par To support a desktop installation, the application developer can use the Application Manager to automatically download the appropriate .cab file to the end user\rquote s 
device. The application developer can write a single desktop setup program that registers the application with AppManager by specifying all the .cab files in the CeAppMgr .ini file. Here is an example of the CeAppMgr .ini file MyApp.ini:
\par }\pard\plain \s39\ql \li0\ri0\sl-220\slmult0\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\f29\fs16\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par [CEAppManager]
\par Version        = 1.0\tab ; this is the CeAppMgr .ini version, not the app version}{\i 
\par }{Component  = MyApplication}{\i 
\par }{
\par [MyApplication]
\par Description   = Sample Windows CE application
\par CabFiles       = MyApp.HPC_SH3.cab,MyApp.PPC_SH3.cab,MyApp.HPCPRO_ARM.cab
\par \tab ; note that there are no extra spaces between the list of .cab files
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
Invoking CeAppMgr with the .ini file registers the application and its associated .cab files, so that the end user can download the application on the next connection.
\par }\pard\plain \s39\ql \li0\ri0\sl-220\slmult0\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\f29\fs16\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\tab <path>\\CEAppMgr.exe "<INI_path>\\MyApp.INI"
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li-1800\ri0\sb200\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin-1800\itap0 \b\f28\fs40\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {For More Information
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {For the latest information about Windows CE, see the
 Windows CE Web site at http://www.microsoft.com/windowsce/. 
\par 
\par }}